# Preset Task Tags Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the steps to allow users to create and use preset tags for their tasks.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [backend/routers/settings.py](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/routers/settings.py)
- Update [get_all_settings](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/routers/settings.py#29-37) to include default `preset_tags` if not already set.
- Default tags: `["Revision", "Assignment", "Reading", "Lecture", "Urgent", "Project", "Research"]`.

### Frontend

#### [MODIFY] [frontend/app/tasks/page.tsx](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/tasks/page.tsx)
- Fetch `preset_tags` from settings on load.
- In [InlineTaskCreator](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/tasks/page.tsx#138-333):
    - Display preset tags as clickable pills.
    - Clicking a pill toggles it in the `tagsInput`.
- In [TaskDetail](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/frontend/app/tasks/page.tsx#481-816):
    - Display preset tags as clickable pills under the Tags input.
    - Clicking a pill toggles it in the `tagsInput`.
- Add a new "Manage Tags" section in settings or a button in the task page to add more presets.


## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Create a task and select preset tags from the list.
- Edit a task and toggle preset tags.
- Update the list of preset tags in the settings (if UI is added, otherwise via API/DB).
